{"/service/ndnp/ohi/batch_ohi_geranium_ver02/data/sn84028102/00340580813/1957081501/0506.xml":{"full_text":"4fr^a#|\n\n\u25a0\u25a0\u25a0_______\nEagle, Mountain Lion\nAre Guests in Chester\nCHESTER Chester has\nsome most unusual guests. They\nare a Golden Eagle by the name\nof Jezebel and Puma or Moun\ntain lion better known as Cleo\npatra.\nJezebel so named because the\nhabits of the Golden eagle re\nsembles very much those of Jez\nbel in the Bible. Jezebel is four\nHI\ni\nSr\nW\n4/\n4\u00bb\nand one half years old.\nCleopatra, now eight months\nold is about four feet long and\nweighs 50 pounds, was captured\nin the wild state in the moun\ntains near San Diego, Calif.\nLou Gaeta of Cleveland, an\nanimal psychologist, is the own\ner of these interesting creatures.\nAt present Mr. Gaeta and his\nv\nI\nWLiil\nk\n/JU\nV^V\": Mr*\u25a0'^wjjroRl\n480\nbaby baths\na day!\njSlli\nat your Service\nNew, \u201cfast recovery\u201d electric water heaters produce hot water\nas fast as you can use it. The average 40-gallon model delivers\n72 gallons of hot, hot water in two hours or 420 gallons a day!\nThat\u2019s more than three times the average family\u2019s daily hot\nwater needs\u2019 So if you want plenty of hot water-fast, get a \u201cfast\nrecovery\u201d electric water heater now.\nA flameless electric water heater costs less to buy\u2014up to 40%\nless than any other kind. And you can install it anywhere. Out\nside of heater always stays cool. No flues or vents are needed.\n\u201cPupils\u201d are staying at the hom\nof Robert Barnes.\nMr. Gaeta is training the pu\nma and shows what can be ac\ncomplished by kindness and un\nderstanding of animals with a\ncertain amount of disciplin. Cle\nopatra is very affectionate and\nresponds to his teachings. He\nuses the animal in visual edu\ncation programs.\nThe eagle is used in a lec\nture on the sport of kings-Fal\nconry. A motion picture has\nbeen prepared showing this bird\nin actual training and hunting.\nThese animals are used In\nTV shows, school assembly pro-\nIf you drive a Buick or Oldsmobile from\nus or even one of our good used cars it\nwill be very, very seldom you\u2019ll ever need\nemergency road service.\nBut when things do go wrong we\u2019re on\nthe job ready to give you prompt, efficient\nservice at moderate prices.\nAnd that\u2019s only one of the many reasons\nwhy, if you live in Geauga county, you\u2019ll\ndo better to buy your next car here.\nM. J. Farinacci\nYour Buick- Oldsmobile Dealer\nRoute 6 Just east from Chardon Square\nTelephone Chardon 5-2137\nw- 4,^?\n&v\u00bbx\nL.-W-\nMg\nifs\na?\nA\nA\nIfs possible with a fast recovery electric water heater\ni\nGeauga Fair Opening\nOnly 3 Weeks Away\nWhen Geauga\u2019s 134th annual\nfair opens in Burton three weeks\nfrom today it will really open\nup with a bang- a \u201ccrash bang\u201d,\nthat is.\nThe spine tingling opening will\nbe provided by the nationally\ngrams and other entertainments.\nGeata and his \u201ctroop\u201d have just\nreturned from Toledo where he\npresented a series of programs.\ni\nr-\nrU\nI\ns\ni\nJ*:\nSpecial Low Rates\nIt\u2019s safe, clean and completely automatic \u2014nothing to light,\nnothing to \u201cgo out,\u201d nothing to attract curious youngsters.\nfamous Jack Kochman \u201cHell\nDrivers\u201d, one of the most pop\nular automobile thrill shows in\nthe country.\nThe show will appear at the\ngrandstand on Thursday even\ning, August 29th, and will fea\nture twenty-eight events in a\nspectacular hour and forty five\nminute program. Included in the\npresentation are ramp-to-ramp\njumps, T-bone crashes, roll-ov-\nThe\n5\nA\nU\ni A\nIn\nUPTOWN\nRestaurant\nGOOD FOOD\nPLEASANT ATMOSPHERE\nREASONABLE PRICES\nMAIN STREET\nCHARDON, OHIO\nIk\nCOMRftNX\nft JP\nI A- ew\nwhen you use an electric water heater of\n30-gallon capacity or more. For full information, call your nearest\nIlluminating Company office.\nALWAYS AT YAH SERVICE IN YK BEST '\\LOCATIAN IN TNE NATIAN*\n5Tf\n\u25a0BE\nFl YOUR SERVICE,,, most TV and radio repairs can bo\nmade from parts carried in our service trucks no need to\nbring your TV or radio to our shop in most cases.\n\u201cCHAD\u201d\nTHRASHER RADIO TV\nMain st., Chardon Ph. 5-8591\nI*-\u2019%\ners and \u201cthrough-the-wall\u201d col\nlisions.\nFair officials have planned the\nlargest fair of all time for the\nthousands of visitors who will\nbe attending the five day festivi\nties in Burton. \u201cWe have plan\nned something for everyone\u201d, of\nficials stated, \u201cand believe this\nto be the best fair ever held in\nGauga County\u201d, they added.\nFarm exhibits, livestock and\nmachinery displays will cover\nmany acres of the fairgrounds.\nConcessions and midway attrac\ntions will be numerous and the\neducational and wildlife collec\ntions larger than ever before.\nIncluded in the list of grand\nstand attractions is a horse\nshow, 4pH program and parade,\nNBC\u2019s \u201cMidwester Hayride\u201d tel\nevision show, stock car racing,\nfireworks and horse pulling con\ntests. The famous Geauga Coun\nty Fair Band will be featured\nin a series of concerts through\nout the five day presentation of\nthe fair.\nCancer Kills 41\nGeaugans in \u201956\nGeauga County had 41 deaths\ndue to cancer in 1956, it was\nlearned at the July meeting of\nthe Geauga Cancer Unit held at\ncancer headquarters in Chardon\non July 22nd. At the present\ntime, 21 patients are receiving\nservices from the local cancer\nunit, four new patients having\nbeen added since May.\nMrs. Sarah Haber er, chair\nman of the surgical dressings\ngroup, reported that there had\nbeen an increase of between 2100\nand 2200 requests for dressings\nin two months.\nMrs. Pauline Haney, Mrs. Ste\nphen Forrest and Mrs. oy\nCoats were appointed by Mrs.\nNewton Chapman, president of\nthe Geauga Cancer Unit, to\nmake arrangements for a can\ncer display at the Geauga Coun\nty Fair over Labor Day week\nend.\nin Crash Here\nTwo cars were slightly dam\naged in an accident in Chardon\nTownship on Rt. 44 one mile\nsouth of the Lake County line\nSunday, August 4, according to\nsheriff\u2019s department reports.\nHarley Furber of Chardon was\ndriving south of Rt. 44 and was\nabout to turn into his driveway\nwhen a car driven by John D.\nPuppel of Perry hit Furber\u2019s\ncar in the lift side. Mr. Puppel\nsaid he didn\u2019t see Mr. Furber\nsignal.\nBowling Season\nOpens Soon\nThe new bowling season is al\nmost ready to get underway.\nAny teams interested in joining\na league may call V recrea\ntion in Chardon.\nThis Thrusday night, August\n15, the early Thursday night and\nearly Monday night leagues will\nmeet at the alleys.\nSubscribe to the\nGeauga Record\nThe\nWelcome Wagon\nHostess\nWill knock on Your Door\nwith Gifts and Greetings\nfrom Friendly Business\nNeighbors and Your\nCivic and Social\nWelfare Leaders\nOn the occasion of\nArrivals of Newcomers to\nCity\nThe Birth of a Baby\nEngagement Announce*\nments\nBetsy Schrader\nChardon 6*5751\nAnn DeMuth\nChardon 6*5315\nHelen Shaffer\nPArk 9*7642\nEleanor Oliver\nMiddlefield, Huntsburg and\nBurton E. Clar. 6*6485\nAnn Giblin\nNewbury TE 4*8364\nLynette Allin\nPA 9*7530\nTHE RECORD, CHARDON, OHIO, AUGUST 15, 1957\u201411\nChardon Man Earns Degree at Ohio U\nRaymond W. Hurd of Bass\nLake Rd., Chardon, was one of\nlittle-car\nbudget\nens, on August 10.\nMr. Hurd, who will teach in\n179 graduates to receive a de- Ch\"*n \u00bbchool system this\nfall, received \u201c\u201crter ef ed\u201d\ngree from Ohio University, Ath- catiOn degree.\nfall, received a master of edu-\nNow you can\nbuy big on a\nSTARTLING FACT\n5 out of 10 Smaller Cars\nwear a Pontiac Price Tag\n-yet none gives you Any\nof Pontiac\u2019s Advantages\nPONTIAC GIVES YOU UP TO 8.9% 1\nMORE SOLID CAR PER DOLLAR.\nNot one of the smaller cars can give you\nthe heavy-duty construction, the\nroad-hugging heft and solid security of\nAmerica\u2019s Number One Road Car!\nPONTIAC GIVES YOU\n4 TO 7 INCHES MORE WHEELBASE.\nHere\u2019s extra length where it coun